<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1861-08-21T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1861-08-21T00:00:00-05:00" n="295" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d295">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Seward</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Harvey</persName></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 7.]</seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of
                                    State</hi>,<lb/><placeName><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>,</placeName>
                                <date calendar="gregorian" when="1861-08-21"><hi rend="italic">August</hi> 21, 1861</date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Your despatch No. 4, under the date of
                            July 20, has been received. Your address to his Majesty was appropriate,
                            and even happy. His reply is very gratifying to this government.</p>
                        <p>We trust that you may find it easy to keep the relations between the two
                            countries on a basis of mutual and cordial friendship.</p>
                        <p>I am, sir, respectfully, your obedient servant,</p>
                        <closer><signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed></closer>
                        <postscript>
                            <p><hi rend="smallcaps">James E. Harvey</hi>, Esq., <hi rend="italic">&amp;c., &amp;c., &amp;c., Lisbon</hi>.</p>
                        </postscript>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>